@section The @code{*Pending*} buffer
@cindex Pending buffer

@kbd{M-x pending-list} opens a tabulated-list view with one row per
registered placeholder.

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .12 .73
@headitem Column @tab Width @tab Meaning
@item ID      @tab 16 @tab Generated symbol name (@code{pending-N}).
@item Buffer  @tab 24 @tab Buffer hosting the placeholder.
@item Label   @tab 30 @tab The label string, truncated.
@item Status  @tab 12 @tab Status keyword, e.g. @code{:streaming}.
@item Elapsed @tab  8 @tab Wall-clock seconds since creation.
@item ETA     @tab  8 @tab The placeholder's ETA, or @samp{-}.
@item Group   @tab 10 @tab The placeholder's group symbol, or @samp{-}.
@end multitable

Bindings:

@table @kbd
@item g
@findex pending-list-refresh
Re-read the registry.
@item RET
@findex pending-list-jump
Pop to the placeholder's buffer.
@item c
@findex pending-list-cancel
Cancel; reason @code{:cancelled-from-list}.
@item q
Bury the buffer.
@end table

The list does not auto-refresh in v0.1; press @kbd{g} to update.
Auto-refresh is on the v0.2 roadmap.

@section Cancel from point

@kbd{M-x pending-cancel-at-point} cancels the placeholder under
point.  The library installs an overlay keymap on every placeholder
binding @kbd{RET} and @kbd{mouse-1} to the same command:

@defvr Variable pending-region-map
@vindex pending-region-map
Keymap installed on placeholder overlays.  Bound to @kbd{RET} and
@kbd{mouse-1} for @code{pending-cancel-at-point}.
@end defvr

@section The demo
@cindex demo

@deffn Command pending-demo
@findex pending-demo
Open @code{*pending-demo*} with three concurrent placeholders
demonstrating the spinner, ETA, and percent indicators.  They resolve
