@end deffn


@node Mode-line lighter
@chapter Mode-line lighter
@cindex mode-line lighter
@cindex global-pending-lighter-mode

@deffn Command global-pending-lighter-mode
@findex global-pending-lighter-mode
A global minor mode that appends a small construct to
@code{global-mode-string}.  When enabled, the mode-line displays:

@example
 [3@U{23F3}~5s]
@end example

Meaning: @emph{3 active placeholders; the smallest remaining ETA
across them is approximately 5 seconds}.  When no placeholder has an
ETA in the future, the trailing tilde-segment is omitted:
@code{[3@U{23F3}]}.  When no placeholders are active, the lighter is
hidden entirely.

The lighter is propertized with @code{pending-spinner-face}, carries
a help-echo tooltip, and binds @kbd{mouse-1} to @code{pending-list}.
@end deffn

@deffn Function pending-mode-line-string
@findex pending-mode-line-string
Compute the lighter string.  Return a propertized string or nil.
Suitable for incorporating manually into a custom mode-line construct
without enabling the global mode.
@end deffn


@node Customization
@chapter Customization
@cindex customization

@section User options

@defopt pending-fps
Animation rate of pending placeholders, in frames per second.  Used
by the single global animation timer that walks the registry on each
tick.  A value of 10 (default) is the conventional sweet spot for
in-buffer spinners --- fast enough to read as motion, slow enough not
to hammer redisplay.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-bar-width
Width of the textual progress bar, in cells.  Default 16.  Used by
the @code{:percent} and @code{:eta} indicators.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-default-spinner-style
Default key into @code{pending-spinner-styles} for new placeholders.
Default @code{'dots-1}.  Per-placeholder override available via the
@code{:spinner-style} keyword to @code{pending-make}.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-spinner-styles
Alist mapping spinner style symbols to vectors of frame strings.
Built-in styles: @code{dots-1}, @code{dots-2}, @code{line},
@code{arc}, @code{clock}.  Add your own with @code{add-to-list}.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-bar-style
Bar character set: @code{eighths} (Unicode eighth-block characters,
default) or @code{ascii} (ASCII fallback for terminals where Unicode
block elements don't render).
@end defopt

@defopt pending-bar-family
Font family used for the progress bar segment, or nil.  When non-nil,
the bar text is rendered in this family so that proportional buffer
faces do not break alignment.  When nil, the bar inherits the
surrounding face --- variable-pitch users may then see misalignment.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-allow-read-only
If non-nil, allow placement of placeholders in read-only buffers.
By default @code{pending-make} refuses to operate on a buffer where
@code{buffer-read-only} is non-nil; setting this to t binds
@code{inhibit-read-only} during insertion and resolution.  Useful for
hosts like @code{compilation-mode} or chat buffers that flip
read-only on the caller's behalf.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-label-max-width
Maximum width, in characters, of a placeholder's visible label.
Default 60.  Labels longer than this are truncated with an ellipsis;
the full label remains available in the placeholder's tooltip.
@end defopt

@defopt pending-confirm-on-emacs-exit
If non-nil, prompt before exiting Emacs while placeholders are
active.  Implemented via @code{pending--kill-emacs-query}, which is
registered on @code{kill-emacs-query-functions} at load time.  When
nil (the default) the query function returns t unconditionally and
the exit is not blocked.
@end defopt

@section Faces
@cindex faces

The library never adds a @code{face} text property to text it
inserts itself.  Faces are applied only to overlay properties ---
the overlay's @code{face} (when adopting an existing region with
@code{BEG < END}), the overlay's @code{before-string} lighter, and
the overlay's @code{after-string} progress bar.  This means the
surrounding buffer's font-lock is never disturbed by the
placeholder library.

@deffn Face pending-highlight
@findex pending-highlight
The overlay @code{face} for adopt-mode placeholders that cover
existing buffer text (@code{BEG < END}).  In insert mode and
zero-width adopt mode the overlay carries no face.  The library
never applies this (or any) face as a text property to text it
inserts itself.
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-lighter
@findex pending-lighter
Static badge shown at BEG of a pending overlay.  Bold white-on-red
by default for high visibility.  The lighter is a visual badge
attached to the overlay's @code{before-string}, not text in the
buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-face
@findex pending-face
Default value of @code{pending-make}'s @code{:face} keyword.
Inherits from @code{pending-highlight}.  Used as the overlay's
@code{face} property only when the overlay covers existing buffer
text (adopt mode with a non-empty range).
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-spinner-face
@findex pending-spinner-face
The before-string spinner glyph.
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-progress-face
@findex pending-progress-face
The after-string progress bar and ETA text.  Apply
@code{pending-bar-family} on top of this face when set, to keep
alignment under variable-pitch buffer faces.
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-error-face
@findex pending-error-face
Retained for backward compatibility and customization.  As of
v0.1.0 the library does not face inserted text --- @code{pending-reject}
inserts plain buffer text and surrounding font-lock applies.
@end deffn

@deffn Face pending-cancelled-face
@findex pending-cancelled-face
Retained for backward compatibility and customization.  As of
v0.1.0 the library does not face inserted text --- @code{pending-cancel}
inserts plain buffer text and surrounding font-lock applies.
@end deffn


@node Hooks and callbacks
@chapter Hooks and lifecycle callbacks
@cindex hooks
@cindex callbacks

@section Per-placeholder callbacks

@subsection @code{:on-cancel}
@cindex on-cancel

Called @emph{before} the cancellation pipeline runs.  Abort
underlying work here --- kill processes, abort gptel requests, cancel
timers.

@example
(pending-make (current-buffer)
              :label "Calling Claude"
              :on-cancel (lambda (p)
                           (gptel-abort (pending-buffer p))))
@end example

If @code{:on-cancel} signals an error or @code{quit}, the cancel
pipeline catches it and proceeds; the placeholder cannot get
stranded.

@subsection @code{:on-resolve}
@cindex on-resolve

Called @emph{once} on transition to any terminal state
(@code{:resolved}, @code{:rejected}, @code{:cancelled},
@code{:expired}).  Inspect @code{(pending-status p)} inside the
callback to differentiate.

@example
(pending-make (current-buffer)
              :label "Calling Claude"
              :on-resolve (lambda (p)
                            (message "Done: %s -> %s"
                                     (pending-label p)
                                     (pending-status p))))
@end example

@section Global hooks installed by the library

@table @code
@item kill-buffer-hook
Buffer-local.  Cancels every placeholder in the buffer being killed
with reason @code{:buffer-killed}.

@item kill-emacs-query-functions
When @code{pending-confirm-on-emacs-exit} is non-nil, prompts before
exit if active placeholders exist.

@item window-buffer-change-functions
Re-arms the parked animation timer when a placeholder's buffer
becomes visible.
@end table

@code{pending-unload-function} cleans up the timer and removes the
global hooks on @code{unload-feature}.

@section Errors
@cindex errors

@deffn Error pending-error
The library's own error symbol.  Signalled by @code{pending-make} for
invalid arguments (dead buffer, read-only buffer when not allowed,
mismatched START/END, out-of-bounds positions).
@end deffn


@node Comparison
@chapter Comparison with @code{org-pending}
@cindex org-pending
@cindex comparison

Bruno Barbier's @code{org-pending} is a closely related upstream Org
patch (branch @code{bba-pending-contents}) that nevertheless declares
itself independent of Org mode.  It solves a similar problem from a
different angle.

@multitable @columnfractions .20 .40 .40
@headitem Aspect @tab @code{org-pending} @tab @code{pending}
@item Distribution
@tab Org-mode patch
@tab Standalone library

@item Org dependency
@tab None (but namespace and prefix imply Org)
@tab None

@item State machine
@tab @code{:scheduled @U{2192} :pending @U{2192} :success/:failure}
@tab Adds @code{:running}, @code{:streaming}, @code{:cancelled},
@code{:expired}

@item Animation
@tab Static Unicode glyph
@tab Animated spinner (10 fps, single global timer)

@item Progress bar
@tab Single line of text in @code{after-string}
@tab Eighth-block Unicode bar (or ASCII fallback)

@item Streaming
@tab Message-passing via @code{org-pending-send-update}
@tab First-class @code{pending-stream-insert} /
@code{-stream-finish}

@item Description UI
@tab @code{*Region Lock*} describe buffer
@tab Tabulated list (deferred describe-buffer)

@item Indirect buffers
@tab Read-only projection
@tab Not yet --- single-buffer scope

@item Kill-emacs query
@tab Built in
@tab Same hook, gated by @code{pending-confirm-on-emacs-exit}
@end multitable

The two libraries can coexist.  Pick whichever suits your caller: if
you live in Org and want minimal animation, prefer
@code{org-pending}; if you want streaming and progress visualization
out of the box, prefer @code{pending}.


@node Caveats
@chapter Limitations and caveats
@cindex caveats
@cindex limitations

@itemize @bullet
@item @strong{~50 placeholders per buffer guideline.}  Each
placeholder is an overlay, and overlays have O(n) scan cost for
some buffer operations.  Keep concurrent counts modest.

@item @strong{Variable-pitch alignment.}  The @code{:percent} and
@code{:eta} bars assume a monospaced cell width.  Under
variable-pitch buffer faces, the bar may look ragged.  Set
@code{pending-bar-family} to a fixed-pitch family to compensate.

@item @strong{No SVG spinner in v0.1.}  Spinners are text glyphs
only.  SVG spinners (and a fringe-bitmap indicator) are on the v0.2
roadmap.

@item @strong{Manual refresh of @code{*Pending*} list.}  Press
@kbd{g} to update; the list does not auto-refresh on registry
mutation in v0.1.

@item @strong{Single-buffer scope.}  A placeholder's overlay and
read-only text properties live in one buffer.  There is no
projection across indirect buffers in v0.1; @code{org-pending}-style
indirect-buffer projection is on the roadmap.

@item @strong{No cross-buffer multi-region pending.}  A single
pending struct represents one contiguous region in one buffer.
Coordinate multiple related placeholders via the @code{:group}
keyword and @code{pending-list-active}.
@end itemize


@node Roadmap
@chapter Roadmap
@cindex roadmap
@cindex v0.2

Items deferred past the v0.1.0 tag:

@itemize @bullet
@item Auto-refresh of @code{*Pending*} on registry mutation.
@item Pulse-on-resolve flash via @code{pulse.el}.
@item @code{pending-as-promise} adapter for @code{aio} users.
@item SVG spinner for graphical frames.
@item Fringe bitmap indicator beside the placeholder.
@item @code{*Region Lock*}-style description buffer for a single
placeholder.
@item Indirect-buffer projection of read-only properties.
@item @code{pending-test--with-mocked-time} macro for deterministic
fast-forward testing.
@end itemize


@node Development
@chapter Development
