@section Building

This package uses @uref{https://github.com/emacs-eask/cli, Eask} for
build automation, with a Makefile wrapper.

@example
# Install dependencies
eask install-deps

# Compile (warning-free)
eask compile

# Run tests (72 ERT tests as of v0.1.0)
eask test ert pending-test.el

# All-in-one via Make
make compile
make test
make docs       # build doc/pending.info
make clean
@end example

@section Generating the manual

The Texinfo source lives at @file{doc/pending.texi}; the built
@file{pending.info} ships in the package.

@example
make info       # build doc/pending.info
make html       # build doc/pending.html (preview)
make clean-docs
@end example

@section Interactive development

@example
;; Reload the library after editing
(unload-feature 'pending t)
(load-file "pending.el")

;; Run a single test
M-x ert RET pending-test/scheduled-to-resolved RET

;; Open the demo
M-x pending-demo
@end example

@section Contributing

Bug reports and pull requests are welcome via GitHub.  When filing
an issue, please include the Emacs version, whether you are running
graphical or terminal Emacs, steps to reproduce, and a backtrace if
applicable.

When sending a PR, please match the existing code style (lexical
binding, double-dash for internal symbols, comprehensive docstrings),
add ERT tests for new behaviour, ensure @code{eask compile} is
warning-free and @code{eask test} is green, and run @kbd{M-x
checkdoc} on touched files.


